org.jgentleframework.configure.objectmeta
Class Binder

java.lang.Object
  org.jgentleframework.configure.AbstractConfigModule

          org.jgentleframework.configure.BindingConfigImpl
              org.jgentleframework.configure.objectmeta.Binder
All Implemented Interfaces:
BindingConfig, CoreBinding
public class Binder
extends BindingConfigImpl

This class manages all necessary information including the meta objects ( ObjectBindingConstant, ObjectAttach, ObjectConstant, ObjectBindingInterceptor, ...) in order to instantiate bean.

On the other hand, it looks like similar to abstract configurable class (extension of Configurable interface or AbstractConfig) class which provide a few methods in order to configure bean instance, however there is a difference that the configurable class is only runable at startup time (configuration time) while Binder is only used at run-time.

In addition, it provides some static method in order to create object metas ( ObjectAttach, ObjectConstant, ObjectBindingConstant, ObjectBindingConstant, ...)
